issues.title: Mark for unmaintained/deprecated libraries
issues.body:
I think we need the annotation for unmaintained/deprecated libraries.
For example, [brain](https://github.com/harthur/brain), neural networks library for JavaScript, is not maintained now.

So it will be worth to mark it like "[W]" (W means warning) or "[UNMAINTAINED]", etc.

comments_data.body:
Sounds nice.
But how can we guess which deprecated project or inactive stable one?

Sorry, I looked brain's description.
It is reasonable to annotate libraries which author says deprecated. :+1:
Sounds good to me also.

@josephmisiti Thank you for the replay.

Next, I think we have to think about the definition of "unmaintained/deprecated".
1. Repository's owner explicitly say that "this library is not maintained".
2. Not committed for long time (2~3 years?)

There is a idea that unless the owner shows the will, we do not mark it (1 only). 
But some repositories are not committed for long time... So it is difficult problem, and we need the criteria to do it.
Sorry for the delay, I think (2) makes more sense.

Sorry for the long waiting time.
I added the description about deprecated repository on the top of the README (Pull #251).
Thank you for your quick action!

issues.title: Added Karate Club an unsupervised machine learning extension library
issues.body: Karate Club consists of state-of-the-art methods to do unsupervised learning on graph structured data. To put it simply it is a Swiss Army knife for small-scale graph mining research. First, it provides network embedding techniques at the node and graph level. Second, it includes a variety of overlapping and non-overlapping community detection methods. Implemented methods cover a wide range of network science (NetSci, Complenet), data mining (ICDM, CIKM, KDD), artificial intelligence (AAAI, IJCAI) and machine learning (NeurIPS, ICML, ICLR) conferences, workshops, and pieces from prominent journals.
